	"type": "feat",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p>When the mutant warrior has fewer than all of its hit points, its flesh attempts to knit itself together, spewing volatile organic compounds as it does so.</p><br><p>All creatures within 5 ft. of the mutant warrior, including the mutant warrior, must succeed on a DC 13 contitution saving throw or take 2d6 poison damage (which the mutant warrior is resistant to). Then, if this doesn't kill the mutant warrior, the mutant warrior regains 5 hit points.</p><br><p>If the mutant warrior isn't in danger and is at 15 hit points or greater, assume that it can regain all hit points over the course of 10 minutes without any danger.</p>",
